Problem:
class TemperatureController {
    private double temperature;
    private boolean heaterOn;

    public TemperatureController() {
        temperature = 20.0; // Room temperature in Celsius
        heaterOn = false;
    }

    public void updateTemperature(double externalTemp) {
        if (heaterOn) {
            temperature += 0.5; // Heater effect
        } else {
            temperature += (externalTemp - temperature) * 0.1; // Natural temperature equalization
        }
    }

    public void toggleHeater() {
        heaterOn = !heaterOn; // Toggle the state of the heater
    }

    public double getTemperature() {
        return temperature;
    }

    public boolean isHeaterOn() {
        return heaterOn;
    }
}",

By observing that the temperature remains steady, can we infer the heater was turned on following an initial drop in external temperature?
